Hi Stephen,=20

=20

Thanks for the mail, on review as this is a commercial vehicle, the =
valuations within the guides are excluding VAT. As we were advised the =
vehicle owner is not VAT registered our valuation includes VAT as per =
the FOS guidelines. The TPI have made no allowance for this, had they =
done so their valuation is actually higher than ours at =C2=A318,780! =
The may want to review, alternatively you could see if they=E2=80=99ll =
settle at their value plus VAT.=20

=20

With regards to the salvage we consider the rate within our report as =
fair and reasonable considering the vehicles value, the repair costs =
exceeding the vehicle value, and the salvage category applied.  The TP =
rate will be based on their increased purchasing power/agreements with =
salvage agents, something the client will not be privy to on the open =
market.

=20

We see no reason to deviate from our report.=20

